<br>
Hmmm...more detail huh?  Heh...ok, what you do for a 'chanter is collect the pages specific to your class (Tasarin's Grimoire, Velishoul's Tome, Sali's Writ, and Nitilim's Grimoire).  These can drop off of anything, there is no certain critter anywhere that drops them.  Generally pages for a certain spell will be found on critters within a few levels of that spell.  So pages for Levitate will be on stuff 15-18'ish or so, since it's level 16.  Generally, the pages are found on MOBs higher that the spell level, so you're more likely to find it on one 16+.  Yet another annoying ploy from Verant to get us to group.  ;-)<br>
<br>
Anyway, once you have the pages required for a certain spell, you put them in a Tome of Endless Enchantments (bought at 'chanter guild) and hit Combine.  If you succeed, ya got a new spell.  If not, you're back out smooshin stuff looking for pages.<br>
<br>
Probably the best site I've found for this is eq.castersrealm.com.  Go to the enchanter class section and you can read a list of all the researchable spells and what pages they require.  This section also details the Concordance of Research quests.  This is basically a way to raise your research skills without wasting pages, so you have a better chance of success.  It's really a pain in the butt to do, but some think it's worth it.  Not one of my chars have done it though, as for the most part pages are pretty easy to find.<br>
<br>
Anyway, that's the basics of it.  Check out CastersRealm for the spell lists, and as always, feel free to spam me in game if you have any question.  :-)<br>
<br>
Teynor<br>
